      "content": "but i thought you just said religious freedom was a \"fundamental right\" earlier? so it feels like you're kinda changing your mind now that i've brought up the other side. isn't a \"fundamental right\" supposed to be protected even when it's inconvenient for society? how do you actually balance that without just picking one side over the other?",
